slims in Bulgaria per Province.svg|thumb|300px|right|Distribution of Muslims in Bulgaria]]\nA table showing the results of the '''2001''' census in Bulgaria regarding religious self-identification:\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n'''The Turkish population in Bulgaria by confession'''\n|- style=\"background:#e0e0e0;\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Professing group\n! colspan=\"2\" | Adherents from the Turkish population\n! colspan=\"2\" | Adherents from the total population\n|- style=\"background:#e0e0e0;\"\n! Number\n! %\n! Number\n! %\n|-\n| [[Islam in Bulgaria|Muslims]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 713,024\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 95.5\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 966,978\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 12.2\n|-\n| Irreligious\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 23,146\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 3.1\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 308,116\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 3.9\n|-\n| [[Eastern Orthodox Church|Orthodox Christians]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 5,425\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 0.7\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 6,552,751\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 82.6\n|-\n| [[Roman Catholicism in Bulgaria|Roman Catholic]] Christians\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 2,561\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 0.3\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 43,811\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 0.6\n|-\n| [[Protestantism in Bulgaria|Protestant]] Christians\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 2,066\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 0.3\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 42,308\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 0.5\n|-\n| Others\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 442\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 0.1\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 14,937\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 0.2\n|-\n| Total population\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| '''746,664'''\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 100.0\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| '''7,928,901'''\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 100.0\n|- style=\"background:#e0e0e0;\"\n|colspan=5|<small>Source: '''2001''' census</small>:<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.nsi.bg/Census/StrReligion.htm | title = Structure of the population by confession | publisher = NSI | access-date = 14 May 2012 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20091225163107/http://www.nsi.bg/Census/StrReligion.htm | archive-date = 25 December 2009 | url-status = dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.nccedi.government.bg/page.php?category=92&id=247 | title = Ethnic minority communities | publisher = NSI | url-status = dead | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20170824222635/http://www.nccedi.government.bg/page.php?category=92&id=247 | archivedate = 24 August 2017 | df = dmy-all }}</ref>\n|}\n\n===Language===\n[[File:Bulgaria ethnic map.png|thumb|Distribution of the mother tongues by municipalities according to the 2011 census in Bulgaria]]\nA table showing the results of the '''2001''' census in Bulgaria regarding linguistic self-identification:\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n'''The Turkish population in Bulgaria by mother tongue'''\n|- style=\"background:#e0e0e0;\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Mother tongue\n! colspan=\"2\" | Speakers from the Turkish population\n! colspan=\"2\" | Speakers from the total population\n|- style=\"background:#e0e0e0;\"\n! Number\n! %\n! Number\n! %\n|-\n| [[Turkish language|Turkish]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 720,136\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 96.4\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 762,516\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 9.6\n|-\n| [[Bulgarian language|Bulgarian]]\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 26,147\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 3.5\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 6,697,158\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 84.5\n|-\n| Others and unspecified\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 381\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 0.1\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 469,227\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 5.9\n|-\n| Total population\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| '''746,664'''\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 100.0\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| '''7,928,901'''\n| style=\"text-align:right;\"| 100.0\n|- style=\"background:#e0e0e0