011 was 2,381.<ref>http://www.ine.pt/ngt_server/attachfileu.jsp?look_parentBoui=165404348&att_display=n&att_download=y</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Alquerubim}}\n[[Category:Parishes of Albergaria-a-Velha]]\n\n\n{{Aveiro-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alquerubim"}
{"title_page": "Alpiar\u00e7a", "text_new": "{{Infobox Portuguese subdivision\n| type            = municipality\n| official_name   = Alpiar\u00e7a\n| image_flag      = Pt-apc1.png\n| image_shield    = APC.png\n| image_skyline   = \n| image_caption   = \n|coordinates             = {{coord|39|15|N|8|34|W|type:adm1st_region:PT_dim:100000|display=inline,title}}\n| image_map       = LocalAlpiarca.svg\n|region             = Alentejo\n|CIM                = [[Lez\u00edria do Tejo]]\n|district           = [[Santar\u00e9m District|Santar\u00e9m]]\n|parishes           = [[#Parishes|1]]\n| leader_party            = [[Unitary Democratic Coalition|CDU]]\n| leader_name             = [[Mario Fernando Pereira]]\n| area_total_km2          = 95.36\n| population_total        = 7,702\n| population_as_of        = 2011\n| holiday         = April 2\n| website                 = http://www.cm-alpiarca.pt\n}}\n'''Alpiar\u00e7a''' ({{IPA-pt|\u0250lpi\u02c8a\u027es\u0250|-|Pt-pt Alpiar\u00e7a FF.ogg}}) is a municipality in [[Santar\u00e9m District]] in Portugal. The population in 2011 was 7,702,<ref>[http://www.ine.pt/xportal/xmain?xlang=en&xpid=INE&xpgid=ine_indicadores&indOcorrCod=0005889&contexto=pi&selTab=tab0 Instituto Nacional de Estat\u00edstica]</ref> in an area of 95.36&nbsp;km\u00b2.<ref name=dgt>{{Cite web |url=http://www.dgterritorio.pt/cartografia_e_geodesia/cartografia/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal_caop_/caop__download_/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal___versao_2017__em_vigor_/ |title=\u00c1reas das freguesias, concelhos, distritos e pa\u00eds |access-date=2018-11-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181105172426/http://www.dgterritorio.pt/cartografia_e_geodesia/cartografia/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal_caop_/caop__download_/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal___versao_2017__em_vigor_/ |archive-date=2018-11-05 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nThe present Mayor is Mario Fernando Pereira and the President of the Municipal Assembly is Mario Santiago. The municipal holiday is April 2.\n\n==Geography==\n\n===Physical geography===\nAlpiar\u00e7a is situated on a plateau in the landscape of the Vale do Tejo-Lez\u00edria. The main town of Alpiar\u00e7a is located at approximately {{convert|20|-|25|m|ft}} above the Tagus Valley, some {{convert|3|km|mi}} from the left bank. The morphology of the terrain is marked by plain profile, sparsely covered by vegetation, and intensely proportioned by its proximity to Tagus, alternating with pasturelands.\n\n===Human geography===\n\nThe municipality of Alpiar\u00e7a includes only one civil parish,<ref>{{cite web|title=Law nr. 11-A/2013, page 552 12|url=http://dre.pt/pdf1sdip/2013/01/01901/0000200147.pdf |accessdate=16 July 2014|author=''[[Di\u00e1rio da Rep\u00fablica]]''|language=Portuguese|format=pdf}}</ref> and is limited in the northeast and east by the municipality of [[Chamusca]], southeast and southwest by the municipality of [[Almeirim]] and northwest by the municipality of [[Santar\u00e9m, Portugal|Santar\u00e9m]].\n\n====International relations====\n{{See also|List of twin towns and sister cities in Portugal}}\nAlpiar\u00e7a municipality is [[Twin towns and sister cities|twinned]] with:\n*{{flagicon|POL}} [[Wysokie Mazowieckie]], [[Poland]]\n*{{flagicon|FRA}} [[Champigny-sur-Marne]], [[France]]\n\n==Architecture==\n\n* Archaeological site of Quinta da Goucha ({{lang-pt|Povoado da Quinta da Goucha/Esta\u00e7\u00e3o arqueol\u00f3gica da Quinta da Goucha/do Cabe\u00e7o da Bruxa}})\n* [[Archaeological site of Quinta dos Patudos]] ({{lang-pt|Castelo de Alpiar\u00e7a/Esta\u00e7\u00f5es arqueol\u00f3gicas da Quinta dos Patudos}})\n* Estate of Quinta dos Patudos ({{lang-pt|Quinta dos Patudos}})\n* Finances Building of Alpiar\u00e7a ({{lang-pt|Edif\u00edcio das Finan\u00e7as de Alpiar\u00e7a}})\n* Manorhouse of Quinta de S\u00e3o Jos\u00e9 ({{lang-pt|Casa da Quinta de S\u00e3o Jos\u00e9}})\n* Residence-Museum of Patudos/Residence of Jos\u00e9 Relvas ({{lang-pt|Casa-Museu dos Patudos/Casa de Jos\u00e9 Relvas}})\n* Theatre of Alpiar\u00e7a ({{lang-pt|Cine-Teatro de Alpiar\u00e7a}})\n\n===Religious===\n* Church of Santo Est\u00e1quio ({{lang-pt|Igreja Paroquial de Alpiar\u00e7a/Igreja de Santo Eust\u00e1quio}})\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.cm-alpiarca.pt/ Town Hall official website]\n*[https://www.flickr.com/photos/vitor107/sets/72057594068058902/ Photos from Alpiar\u00e7a]\n\n{{Municipalities of Santar\u00e9m}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Alpiarca Municipality}}\n[[Category:Municipalities of Portugal]]\n[[Category:Populated places in Santar\u00e9m District]]\n[[Category:Municipalities of Santar\u00e9m District]]\n\n\n{{Santar\u00e9m-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Portuguese subdivision\n| type            = municipality\n| official_name   = Alpiar\u00e7a\n| image_flag      = Pt-apc1.png\n| image_shield    = APC.png\n| image_skyline   = \n| image_caption   = \n|coordinates             = {{coord|39|15|N|8|34|W|type:adm1st_region:PT_dim:100000|display=inline,title}}\n| image_map       = LocalAlpiarca.svg\n|region             = Alentejo\n|CIM                = [[Lez\u00edria do Tejo]]\n|district           = [[Santar\u00e9m District|Santar\u00e9m]]\n|parishes           = [[#Parishes|1]]\n| leader_party            = [[Unitary Democratic Coalition|CDU]]\n| leader_name             = [[Mario Fernando Pereira]]\n| area_total_km2          = 95.36\n| population_total        = 7,702\n| population_as_of        = 2011\n| holiday         = April 2\n| website                 = http://www.cm-alpiarca.pt\n}}\n'''Alpiar\u00e7a''' ({{IPA-pt|\u0250lpi\u02c8a\u027es\u0250|-|Pt-pt Alpiar\u00e7a FF.ogg}}) is a municipality in [[Santar\u00e9m District]] in Portugal. The population in 2011 was 7,702,<ref>[http://www.ine.pt/xportal/xmain?xlang=en&xpid=INE&xpgid=ine_indicadores&indOcorrCod=0005889&contexto=pi&selTab=tab0 Instituto Nacional de Estat\u00edstica]</ref> in an area of 95.36&nbsp;km\u00b2.<ref name=dgt>{{Cite web |url=http://www.dgterritorio.pt/cartografia_e_geodesia/cartografia/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal_caop_/caop__download_/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal___versao_2017__em_vigor_/ |title=\u00c1reas das freguesias, concelhos, distritos e pa\u00eds |access-date=2018-11-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181105172426/http://www.dgterritorio.pt/cartografia_e_geodesia/cartografia/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal_caop_/caop__download_/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal___versao_2017__em_vigor_/ |archive-date=2018-11-05 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nThe present Mayor is Mario Fernando Pereira and the President of the Municipal Assembly is Mario Santiago. The municipal holiday is April 2.\n\n==Geography==\n\n===Physical geography===\nAlpiar\u00e7a is situated on a plateau in the landscape of the Vale do Tejo-Lez\u00edria. The main town of Alpiar\u00e7a is located at approximately {{convert|20|-|25|m|ft}} above the Tagus Valley, some {{convert|3|km|mi}} from the left bank. The morphology of the terrain is marked by plain profile, sparsely covered by vegetation, and intensely proportioned by its proximity to Tagus, alternating with pasturelands.\n\n===Human geography===\n\nThe municipality of Alpiar\u00e7a includes only one civil parish,<ref>{{cite web|title=Law nr. 11-A/2013, page 552 12|url=http://dre.pt/pdf1sdip/2013/01/01901/0000200147.pdf |accessdate=16 July 2014|author=''[[Di\u00e1rio da Rep\u00fablica]]''|language=Portuguese|format=pdf}}</ref> and is limited in the northeast and east by the municipality of [[Chamusca]], southeast and southwest by the municipality of [[Almeirim]] and northwest by the municipality of [[Santar\u00e9m, Portugal|Santar\u00e9m]].\n\n====International relations====\n{{See also|List of twin towns and sister cities in Portugal}}\nAlpiar\u00e7a municipality is [[Twin towns and sister cities|twinned]] with:\n*{{flagicon|POL}} [[Wysokie Mazowieckie]], [[Poland]]\n*{{flagicon|FRA}} [[Champigny-sur-Marne]], [[France]]\n\n==Architecture==\n\n* Archaeological site of Quinta da Goucha ({{lang-pt|Povoado da Quinta da Goucha/Esta\u00e7\u00e3o arqueol\u00f3gica da Quinta da Goucha/do Cabe\u00e7o da Bruxa}})\n* [[Archaeological site of Quinta dos Patudos]] ({{lang-pt|Castelo de Alpiar\u00e7a/Esta\u00e7\u00f5es arqueol\u00f3gicas da Quinta dos Patudos}})\n* Estate of Quinta dos Patudos ({{lang-pt|Quinta dos Patudos}})\n* Finances Building of Alpiar\u00e7a ({{lang-pt|Edif\u00edcio das Finan\u00e7as de Alpiar\u00e7a}})\n* Manorhouse of Quinta de S\u00e3o Jos\u00e9 ({{lang-pt|Casa da Quinta de S\u00e3o Jos\u00e9}})\n* Residence-Museum of Patudos/Residence of Jos\u00e9 Relvas ({{lang-pt|Casa-Museu dos Patudos/Casa de Jos\u00e9 Relvas}})\n* Theatre of Alpiar\u00e7a ({{lang-pt|Cine-Teatro de Alpiar\u00e7a}})\n\n===Religious===\n* Church of Santo Est\u00e1quio ({{lang-pt|Igreja Paroquial de Alpiar\u00e7a/Igreja de Santo Eust\u00e1quio}})\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.cm-alpiarca.pt/ Town Hall official website]\n*[https://www.flickr.com/photos/vitor107/sets/72057594068058902/ Photos from Alpiar\u00e7a]\n\n{{Municipalities of Santar\u00e9m}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Alpiarca Municipality}}\n[[Category:Municipalities of Portugal]]\n[[Category:Populated places in Santar\u00e9m District]]\n[[Category:Municipalities of Santar\u00e9m District]]\n\n\n{{Santar\u00e9m-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alpiar%C3%A7a"}
{"title_page": "Alpendorada, V\u00e1rzea e Torr\u00e3o", "text_new": "{{Infobox Portuguese subdivision \n|type = parish \n|official_name      = Alpendorada, V\u00e1rzea e Torr\u00e3o\n|image_skyline      = \n|image_caption      = \n|image_flag         =\n|image_shield       = \n|image_location     = \n|region             = [[Norte Region, Portugal|Norte]]\n|CIM                = [[T\u00e2mega e Sousa]]\n|district           = [[Porto District|Porto]]\n|municipality       = [[Marco de Canaveses]]\n|coordinates        = {{coord|41.087|-8.243|type:adm1st_region:PT_dim:50000|display=inline,title}}\n|elevation          = \n|area_total         = 16.82\n|population_as_of   = 2011\n|population_total   = 8485\n|patron             = \n|area_code          = \n|postal_code        = \n|website            = \n}}\n'''Alpendorada, V\u00e1rzea e Torr\u00e3o''' is a [[Freguesia (Portugal)|civil parish]] in the municipality of [[Marco de Canaveses]], Portugal. It was formed in 2013 by the merger of the former parishes Alpendurada e Matos, V\u00e1rzea do Douro and Torr\u00e3o.<ref>{{cite web|title=Law nr. 11-A/2013, pages 552 67-68|url=http://dre.pt/pdf1sdip/2013/01/01901/0000200147.pdf |accessdate=5 August 2014|author=''[[Di\u00e1rio da Rep\u00fablica]]''|language=Portuguese|format=pdf}}</ref> The population in 2011 was 8,485,<ref name=ine>[http://www.ine.pt/ngt_server/attachfileu.jsp?look_parentBoui=165404348&att_display=n&att_download=y Instituto Nacional de Estat\u00edstica (INE)], Census 2011 results according to the 2013 administrative division of Portugal</ref> in an area of 16.82&nbsp;km\u00b2.<ref name=dgt>{{Cite web |url=http://www.dgterritorio.pt/cartografia_e_geodesia/cartografia/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal_caop_/caop__download_/carta_administrativa_oficial_de_portugal___versao_2017__em_vigor_/ |title=\u00c1reas das freguesias, concelhos, distritos e pa\u00eds |access-date=2018-11-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181105172426/http://www.dgterritorio.